"Yeah, well, them's the breaks, kid."
> throw shoe

> throw shoe

You hurl the shoe with all your strength at the milk bottles stack.  It connects with a thunderous crash, knocking the bottles all over the floor.

"Ha!' you say proudly, "Told ya I just needed somethin' heavier!"

"That don't count! You were s'posed ta use the beanbag!" cries the barker.

"That ain't what you said. You said I just had ta knock 'em down. You didn't say nothing about how. Now gimmie my prize!"

"Fine." Grumbling, the barker grabs a kewpie doll off the wall behind him and tosses it at you. "Damn kid's gonna put me outta business..."
