You are in a dressing room.
It's a dressing room, full of trunks and boxes as well as several privacy screens -- behind which performers would presumably get ready for the show.  There's also a vanity complete with mirror.  Everything is covered with slippery ichor.
You can see a privacy screen, a vanity and a kerosene lamp.
You can go south.

You hear something stirring out in the alleyway behind you.
> hide behind privacy screen

> hide behind privacy screen
You duck behind the screen just as you hear someone lumber into the room.  Peeking through a gap in the screen, you see that it's the grungy man from the entrance ticket booth.  He plops into the folding chair in front of the vanity and begins to apply clown make-up.

Wait a minute.

No, he's not. He's REMOVING make-up!  Underneath, his skin is ghostly white with splotches of lurid red on his cheeks and around his lips.  He shakes his head and a ruff explodes out from his neck like a peacock unfolding its tail.  He pulls off his shirt to reveal naked skin beneath polka-dotted and baggy like the smock of a clown.

In mere minutes the transformation is complete. Where there was once a man is now a clown.  He lurches to his feet with a final nod at the mirror and lumbers back out of the room.
