> x portrait

> x portrait
A large looming oil painting hangs at an angle on the wall. It depicts a pinch-faced old man in a luxurious peacoat and tophat.  There's a brass plaque at the base of the painting.
> ask Percy about portrait

> ask Percy about portrait
Percy notices you squinting at the plaque.  "Here, let me take a look," he says.

His eyes go wide.  "It says this is 'Bartleby Tastycakes, CEO of Sweetiepie Doll & Novelty Rubberworks.' Good Lord, this...this must have been his office! This entire carnival must be right above the remains of the old factory!"

Percy rubs his chin. "I wonder if this carnival always appears above sites like this? Sites of some great urchin tragedy. Maybe that's why it always takes urchins."

You stare up at the portrait. "I don't like it. He gots a bad mug."
