You can see a wizened old man.
You can go north or south.
> s

> s

You are in the Gallery of Grotesqueries.
You stumble through the beaded curtain into a dim oppressive room, filled with all sorts of bizarre exhibits showcasing the strange and unusual. The only light comes from the single naked electric bulb dangling from a ceiling cord; it casts an evil glare across the rows and rows of dark glass mason jars stacked up in the corners.

You can see a pigmonkey, pickled punks, Petunia Porkchops the fat lady and a jackelope.
You can go north.
> talk to lady

> talk to lady
"Oh honey, ah don't want no clowns in here!... Oh wait, is that you, shugah? Lawdsakes, I plumb didn't recognize ya! Why're you wearin' that awful thing anyways?"
> ask lady about worm

> ask lady about worm
"Lawd sakes, don't talk 'bout such things! Ah don't rightly know what they've got under the big top, but ah reckon it can't be nothin' good.  It's got ta be some sorta ungodly abomination! An' from what ah've heard, it eats even more'n I do. An' ah eat a lot!"
