> ask Percy about zeppelin

> ask Percy about zeppelin
"Wot's it say?" you ask Percy.

"It says 'T.I. Urge & Silent Partners Carnival of Regrets! Urchins Welcome!' "
> x posters

> x posters
The walls are covered with faded posters advertising previous years' carnivals.  You can't read the writing, but you recognize the pictures of famous landmarks indicating that the Carnival of Regrets has visited Stenchport, Massachusetts (site of the infamous Happy Cat cannery fire); Junkheap, Maryland (site of the infamous St. Ursula's Home for Wayward Urchins, Mudlarks and Tatterdemalions mass asbestos poisoning); Industrialized Fumebelch, West Virginia (site of the infamous Candlewick coal mine collapse); and Rotgut, New York (site of the infamous Rotgut karzer beatings).

Huh. It's almost like there's a theme here.
> x hydrogen

> x hydrogen
It's a large cannister of hydrogen, used for inflating zeppelins.
> ask Percy about posters

> ask Percy about posters
"Very odd that this carnival seems to only visit towns where there's been some kind of urchin mass tragedy," says Percy, "I wonder if the lingering psychic energy of the tragedy draws the Dark Carnival to these spots, like hunger draws a possum to a corn hutch. Or perhaps the Dark Carnival is itself somehow spawned from the misery of those tragedies, growing like a fungus in the dark places of the world?"

"Jeez, Percy, you is gettin' pretty heavy with that talk!" you mutter.
> ask Percy about hydrogen

> ask Percy about hydrogen
"Careful, Rags! Hydrogen is highly flammable. You'd better keep that away from any open flames or we'll all be blown to kingdom come!"
