The air is thick with smoke and ash; you can feel the heat billowing from the fire raging inside the Big Top to your north.

T.I. Urge the ringmaster is blocking the exit to the south, speaking in agitated tones to a squat clown dressed in green polka dots.
You can see T. I. Urge.
You can go east, west or south.

"I know that little red-headed sneak did this," snarls T.I. Urge. "I want her found and I want her dealt with."

"Most of the carnies escaped in the chaos, but clowns caught Abracadabragail!" says the squat clown. "Clowns put her over at the bumper cars!"

"I don't care about Abracadabragail! I want Lil' Ragamuffin! I want that... that nasty little urchin and her pet rat too!"

"But she could be anywhere! The circus is on fire! The clownqueror worm is no more!" wails the squat clown. "Clowns must get out or clowns will melt!"

"No one leaves until I get to strangle that urchin with my own hands!"

Cowed, the squat clown ducks away and joins the fray of panicking clowns.
