> s

You are at the Grand Entrance.
The entryway to the carnival is through the mouth of a giant, grinning plywood face with a handlebar mustache and spinning swirly eyes.
You can see a ticket booth and a wanted poster.
You can go north.
Smashing your way through barriers of cloth and burning tar and rubber, you finally see sunlight ahead as the bumper car bursts through the boarded-up carnival entrance. You're free!

"Ha! Ain't no carnival that kin eat Lil' Ragamuffin!" you crow, "Take that, ya stupid ringmaster! That's what I thinka you an' your giant worm!"

Percy twists around in his seat to watch the burning circus tents disappearing into the distance behind you, thick columns of black smoke billowing into the sky.

"It looks like the whole carnival is burning to the ground," he says. "Though honestly, I do believe that's a moot point.  With the clownqueror worm destroyed, the Carnival of Regrets was effectively dead. It couldn't survive without the dark heart that kept it going."

"Good riddance," you say. "I don't care what they call that place, I ain't got no regrets 'bout blowin' it up.

As the bumper car trundles further from the carnival, you start to notice little clusters of people here and there gathered to watch the carnage.  You recognize a few faces: Red and Mugsy staring wide-eyed, the fat lady clutching the struggling pigmonkey in her arms, the strong man biting his nails nervously, Jolly Bottles grinning widely... Looks like the carnies, freed from their dark carnival prison, have gathered to watch their personal hell burn to the ground.

"I can't believe that I'm finally free of that awful dark carnival," says Abracadabragail. "I...  I mean, we, all the carnies... owe you such a debt, Lil' Ragamuffin. We can never repay you! You'll go down in carnie lore as... The Carnival Destroyer!"

"The Carnival Destroyer?" says Percy. "Destroying a whole carnival is certainly something that would, dare I say it, disturb the peace.  Something that might even attract the notice of the Urchinfinder General, perhaps."

"Yeah!" you say, brightening at the prospect as you ride your bumper car off into the sunset. "That's right! Public Enemy Number 1, here I come!"
